The paper deals with the enumeration of fullerene patches, which are 2-connected plane graphs with specific properties. This falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for solving the problem of whether a given sequence is a boundary code of a fullerene patch, which involves graph theory and computational geometry, making categories cs.CG and cs.DS likely as well. The paper also mentions a conjecture and an algorithm for counting the number of different patches with a given boundary code, which could fall under categories cs.GT (combinatorics and graph theory) and cs.CC (computational complexity).
